==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imparisyllabic
<hw>Im*par"i*syl*lab"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impar</ets> unequal + E. <ets>syllabic</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>imparisyllabique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>Not
consisting of an equal number of syllables; <as>as, an
<ex>imparisyllabic</ex> noun, one which has not the same number of
syllables in all the cases</as>; as, <xex>lapis</xex>,
<xex>lapidis</xex>; <xex>mens</xex>, <xex>mentis</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imparity</ent>⟦br⟧
